VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'make sure to like and subscribe. So, when people say, "Just post more listing videos." That sounds easy until you realize what it actually takes. And for somebody who already has a lot on their plate, this is most likely the main thing that\'s going to get pushed off to'

[00:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'the side. For this example, we\'re going to be using a fake real estate agent named Greg, and that\'s what I\'ll be referring to the avatar as. But the goal for today is very simple. Greg wants to post short listing videos consistently, but he doesn\'t want to film himself over and over again every time a new property'

[00:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'hits the market. So, we\'re about to do this in three simple steps. Step one, create the AI avatar. Step two, build a reusable listing prompt. three, turn the video script into an actual video inside of HeyGen. So, without further ado,'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'let\'s get started inside of HeyGen. First, we have to create our avatar, and that\'s going to act as our on-screen presence. So, inside HeyGen, head on over to the main dashboard, and all the way to the left, click avatars. Then at the top right, you want to click the'

[01:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'create avatar button. But now, once you click create, HeyGen\'s going to ask you whether you want a photo avatar or a video avatar. For real estate, and honestly most other content, I would really recommend the video avatar. This is simply because it ends up coming out the most realistic. the setup for this'

[01:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'one\'s a little bit different than a fitness coach or an educational creator. For a fitness coach, a gym setting made sense. And for an educational creator, a desk setup made sense. But for real estate, I would want the avatar to feel professional. That might mean wearing something business casual, maybe'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'standing in a clean home office, or even just sitting in front of a neutral background. Whatever you feel works for you and your brand the most. And now, for actually filming the footage for your avatar, it\'s a lot simpler than you probably think. Aim for just around 2'

[01:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'minutes of clean footage, either filmed in landscape or portrait and ideally 1080p quality or higher. And just make sure you\'re keeping the file size under the limit that HeyGen specifies for you. The main thing with this is that your avatar should look like somebody who you'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'could trust with a high-value decision. And now once the footage is ready, you can drag it into the upload box or click here to look for it. And then you can go ahead and select it from here. From there, HeyGen\'s going to ask you to give your avatar a name and it\'s going to ask if you want to use the voice that it'

[02:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'made for you based off the video you provided or if you want to re-record your own afterwards with the script they give you. I recommend re- cording it and that\'s just because when you do, it usually comes out sounding exactly like you. Sometimes the default one pulled'

[02:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'from your recording can have some flaws. But now you can upload it and move on to the next step and that being the consent step. HeyGen\'s just going to ask you to record a super short consent clip. This is just to confirm that the person being turned into the avatar actually gave'

[02:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'consent to be used as one. And of course, this is incredibly important whether you\'re making this for yourself, a client, a team member or anyone else. But now once you submit, HeyGen will just process your avatar in the background. This can take anywhere from a few minutes to maybe a little bit'

[02:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'longer depending on the size and length of the footage. But to make it easy and so you don\'t have to wait around, HeyGen\'s going to send you a notification when it\'s done. And when it\'s done, you can go ahead and preview it. And now once you\'re happy with your avatar, we have the base asset for our entire content system done. But now this'

[03:07] [scene:talk]
