AUDIO: 'And this is definitely the most important point of the episode because for real estate content, the script is going to change a lot and that\'s obviously due to every listing having varying details. So instead of writing a brand new prompt every single time,'

[03:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'we\'re going to build one master prompt that can take listing details as an input. That way you or my avatar Greg can reuse the same exact prompt for every single listing. Now to make it easy for you, I have already made the master prompt. It\'s going to look and'

[03:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'sound something like this. Act as a real estate copywriter using these listing details, address, beds, baths, square footage, price, three key features, and neighborhood. Write a 45-second social video script. Open with a hook about the'

[03:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'neighborhood or a standout feature. Mention price only if it strengthens the hook. End with DM me for a private tour. Keep the tone conversational, polished, and easy to understand. And if you don\'t understand just quite yet, this is the entire system, not just one prompt, but'

[04:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'a completely reusable template. Because now we can just plug in different listing details every time. So, let\'s plug in the first listing. Listing number one. 24 Oak Ridge Drive, four beds, three baths, 2,450 square feet, $800,000, renovated kitchen, finished'

[04:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'basement, large backyard, located near top-rated schools and local parks. And now, once we submit that, we\'ll get a fully generated script. It can open with the family-friendly neighborhood, mention the renovated kitchen, call out'

